"On tap at Rock Bottom in Denver. Pours hazy yellow with a fluffy white head. Aroma of barnyard funk, some yeast, a hint of salt, tart lemons, wheat malts, some definite sweetness here. Flavor follows the smell closely with tart and sweet lemons and honey, wheat malts, some light saltiness (very light), and a funky yeasty finish. The body on this was pretty light and refreshing, with medium carbonation. This really came off more as a saison to me, but had it side by side with their honey saison and this had a slight salt tinge to it. Other than that, they were very similar."
