"A nice sour beer that has a touch of funk. Crisp and refreshing, the fruit flavors are very bright and only brought down by the grains from the malt. Not an overpowering sour this one is great for a hot summers day or an average spring one in SoCal."
"Pours a light clear golden with almost no head. Appears a bit like apple juice. The nose starts with dry wheat notes and plenty of coriander and lemon zest. The coriander brings on some floral qualities mixed with citrus fruit. The taste is light and refreshing with the salt coming through and cutting into the fruit and light tartness. The finish is heavy on lemon and almost drinks like a shandy. This is ridiculously drinkable and refreshing. Perfect for a warm summer day."
