"well made beer here, but different from other goses i have had, especially on the salt factor. its minimal here, and still adds some body, but doesnt hardly add any dryness or minerality to the beer. hazy blonde brew with a gorgeous tall white head foamy and thick. it smells like just a bit of coriander over a wheat beer, german wheat, dusty and dry, with that coriander seed perfume aromatic. the salt doesnt impact the flavor much here, it may be a little under done in that regard, at least compared to other american made examples of the style, but the beer is quite tasty despite that. the coriander isnt as pungent as it is in the nose, and the yeast does a nice job drying this thing out, cracker dry. a nice lush body gives a lot of character to this wheat driven beer. maybe a little more simple than i was expecting from almanac, who always seems to go crazy with odd yeasts and fruits and methods. this one seems a bit more basic to me, and even underwhelms when held up next to other examples of the gose style, but i like it a lot, find it extremely refreshing, and would happily drink it on the regular this summer if it were available here in colorado."
